🏨 Hotel Booking & Billing System (HBBS)

Developed by: Muhammad Hassaan (2025-CS-440)  
Institution: University of Engineering and Technology (UET), Lahore  
Course: Object-Oriented Programming (Semester 2)

---

📖 Project Overview
The Hotel Booking & Billing System (HBBS) is a comprehensive console-based application developed in C#. It is designed using a strict 3-Tier Architecture (UI, Business Logic, and Data Access Layers) to manage hotel operations efficiently. The system provides role-based access for Administrators and Staff, featuring persistent data storage via File Handling.

✨ Core Features

🛡️ Admin Portal
User Management: Add, remove, and update credentials for Admins and Staff members.
Room Management: Add new rooms, update room prices, and manage room availability status.
System Monitoring: View comprehensive lists of all registered staff, admins, and current room statuses.

🛎️ Staff Portal
Booking Management:Check-in and check-out guests, update booking details, and cancel reservations.
Billing System:Automatically calculate total stay costs and generate invoices upon check-out.
Room Tracking: View all available rooms and active bookings in real-time.

🏗️ System Architecture
This project strictly adheres to the Single Responsibility Principle (SRP) by separating code into three distinct layers:

1. UI Layer (`HBBS.UI`): Handles all Console inputs and outputs. Separated into specific classes (`AdminUI`, `StaffUI`, `RoomUI`, `BookingUI`) for clean routing.
2. Business Logic Layer (`HBBS.BL`): Contains the core entities (`Admin`, `Staff`, `Room`, `Registerations`, `Billing`). Implements OOP concepts like Inheritance, Composition, and Aggregation.
3. Data Layer (`HBBS.DL`): Manages all persistent data through File Handling (`.txt` files). Implements CRUD operations and ensures data integrity across application restarts.
